.TH SRT 1 "2026" "The-JLC-Project" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
srt \- sort lines in a file alphabetically
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B srt
.I file
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B srt
reads all lines from
.IR file ,
sorts them in ascending lexicographic (byte) order, and writes the sorted
lines to standard output.
This is a minimal JLC equivalent of
.BR sort (1).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Wrong number of arguments.
.TP
.B 2
Cannot open file.
.TP
.B 3
Memory allocation failure.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Sort a file:
.EX
srt names.txt
.EE
.TP
Sort and remove duplicates with spec:
.EX
srt words.txt | spec
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sort (1),
.BR spec (1)
.SH AUTHORS
The-JLC-Project contributors.
